cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes an algorithm to recover independent causal mechanisms, which is a central concept in the study of causality and has implications for machine learning tasks. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of experts that compete for data to specialize and extract the mechanisms, which is a common approach in machine learning. The paper also involves image transformations, which suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of unsupervised learning and the discussion of generative modeling also suggest a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY) in the context of causal mechanisms, which further supports the inclusion of these sub-categories.
